{
  "designRationale": {
    "layoutDecisions": "The layout uses Strategy A (Full-Width + Content Sections) because the user requested a full-width hero image.  This prioritizes the visual impact of the car image while allowing for sufficient space for other product details below.",
    "userFlowReasoning": "The user flow is straightforward: view the hero image, then scan key details (title, price, seller info), and finally, take the primary action (Contact Seller).",
    "componentChoices": "I chose the 10:7816 (IMAGES) component for the hero image over a simple 10:7816 (image) component because the user wants a full-width image. This component will allow for the full width display while supporting different aspect ratios.",
    "componentGaps": "User request requires a seller avatar, but the design system lacks a dedicated component that combines an avatar with name and location. I addressed this by using a 10:7773 (avatar / big) component for the avatar image, and native-text components for the seller name and location. This combination provides a clear and visually appealing solution.",
    "visualHierarchy": "Visual hierarchy is established through: 1. Full-width hero image, 2. Large headline for title, 3. Medium headline for price, 4. Body text for seller info.  This guides user attention naturally.",
    "variantSelectionRationale": "For the 10:3907 (Button) component, I selected the \"Size: Large\", \"Type: Filled\", \"Color: Green\", and \"State: Default\" variants.  Large size ensures easy tap target on mobile, filled type provides clear visual feedback, green matches primary action conventions, and default state is for initial display.",
    "nativeElementJustification": "User request requires display of seller name, price, and location text in a specific hierarchy and style.  While native-text supports this, using the system text style \"Headline/Large\" for the product title and \"Headline/Medium\" for price ensures consistency with the design system's established typography."
  }
}
```

